<br>
I adore the flute though. No really. I never got a tiny cloak. :P<br>
<br>
Sorry Lanolar didn't mean to be snippy about it, if you don't have them either, then perhaps you can understand.<br>
<br>
However, here is the thing.<br>
<br>
There are certain items in the game that define our class, for better or for worse. A 3.6 or whatever horn is not really one of them. A 3.4 set of drums is.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because doing that raid content, you kinda need those drums...well ok, perhaps you don't. We certainly seem to manage without them--but it helps I think that we had some breaking into time and for the first four months we were there.<br>
<br>
Other things that define our class...by that I mean you can't really live without: vots (anyone can get), our songs, and the instrument and song aa's. (again, anyone can get those.) Although certainly other instrument mods can be useful, necessary even, nothing but the drums matter much in terms of maxing out the mod. (except voice of course...but with amp, again, anyone can do that.)<br>
<br>
I'm glad there are more out there. We got barxt to 0%...and then we all died. So maybe someday soon we will see them. Agree would be nice if the pox drums mod was raised a little. 3.0 seems fair--would make them sorta worth getting, but not &quot;overpowering.&quot;<br>
<br>
I am not arguing that rathe drums should drop like candy, I am arguing that the aspects that make our class useful and in some cases more fun (cough, water lute), should be something that people get along the way, not something so rare that only a few people get. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talidd>Talidd</A></span><br> Posts: 103<br> <font color=#330000>(6/27/04 6:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19482.topic&index=91>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> The Pox drums are currently 2.9<br>
<br>
Changing them to 3.0 would have very little effect.<br>
<br>
The difference would be like +5 to resists. Changing them to 3.2 would be +15, 3.4=+25<br>
<br>
Aside from the stat difference and the clicky(both very nice), there is really no reason to upgrade from the Pox drums from the TDoK, which is pretty ridiculous.<br>
<br>
<br>
At least setting these to 3.2 mod would be good, and making them a little less common, perhaps. But not as rare as the Rathe drums..All the bards in my guild have (or have had a chance to loot) the Pox drum, but only two have the Rathe drum. Changing these to be about equal would certainly help on times when I'm too lazy to play AE resists! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=duvane>Duvane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.titansofsaryrn.net/andsig.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#330000>(6/28/04 5:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19482.topic&index=92>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Voila, theres a alternative drum found on a even harder mob and as rare as rathe drums ofcourse.<br>
